data.title: The Bear’s Den, July 16, 2024
data.meta_description: Rookies report to Halas Hall today, the process of training camp is underway
data.text:
WE WANT YOU!

Would you like to show your Chicago Bears spirit to the world? I’m starting a feature where Windy City Gridiron readers can share pictures of themselves and their families and friends in Bears attire. Simply email a picture to me at the following address: denmasterken at aol dot com. The pictures need to be clear, and full resolution (i.e. full size from your phone if that’s how you take them). Include any description information you like along with the photo!

THE DAILY SPONGIE SPECIAL

BEARRRSSSS

With rookies to report Tuesday, Bears’ top two picks remain unsigned - Chicago Sun-Times - Quarterback Caleb Williams, the first overall pick, and receiver Rome Odunze, the ninth selection, are among the few NFL rookies yet to ink their deals. They are the two highest selections among the five unsigned first-rounders left.

Photos: Chicago Bears QB Caleb Williams hosts students at foundation event – Chicago Tribune - More than 700 people representing 12 Chicago schools packed the Dr. Conrad Worrill Track and Field Center at Gately Park to greet Chicago Bears quarterback Caleb Williams in the first Chicago event for his Caleb Cares Foundation.

Meet the 2024 Chicago Bears: 89 thoughts on the roster ahead of training camp - The Athletic - All eyes will be on rookie Caleb Williams in training camp, but 88 other players will be competing in Lake Forest as well.

Chicago Bears: 32 players are locks for the 53-man roster - Bears Wire - There’s no doubt these players will make the Bears roster.

Connor Rogers high on DJ Moore as the Bears’ top player for fantasy football – NBC Sports Chicago - Connor Rogers high on DJ Moore as the Bears’ top player for fantasy football

Dave Wannstedt talks all things Chicago Bears training camp – NBC Sports Chicago - Former NFL head coach Dave Wannstedt joins NBC Chicago’s Mike Berman on Sports Sunday to discuss what might be going through Matt Eberflus’ head in the final...

Bears 2024 position preview: Defensive line - Chicago Bears - Star pass rusher Montez Sweat leads a defensive line group that returns four contributors in DeMarcus Walker, Andrew Billings, Gervon Dexter Sr. and Zacch Pickens.

POLISH SAUSAGE

Robbie Gould still roots for 49ers despite "fractured" relationship with front office - NBC Sports - Robbie Gould, 41, has not played since the 2022 season.

Tee Higgins will play 2024 under the franchise tag as deadline for long-term deal passes - NBC Sports - The Bengals WR will be the lone NFL player to play this season on the tag.

Dolphins assessing "significant damage" to Hard Rock Stadium after soccer fiasco - NBC Sports - Hard Rock Stadium suffered "significant damage" during a security breach before the Copa America final in Miami on Sunday night.

IN CASE YOU MISSED IT ON WINDY CITY GRIDIRON

Chicago Bears Top 5 Training Camp Battles Worth Monitoring - Windy City Gridiron - General manager Ryan Poles has done plenty of work to this roster over the last three offseasons. Even so, this is a team that is looking for long-term answers in multiple areas. Here are the five best training camp battles that will hold fan’s attention over the next six weeks.

2024 Chicago Bears Training Camp Preview: Defense and Special Teams - Windy City Gridiron - Robert Schmitz joins the Bears Banter Podcast to help us with our training camp preview!
